    "acceptance_state": "boundary_recorded",
    "claim": "SST-2 and MRPC evaluated with 7 seeds each under e0_dense and e2_l1 (column-norm Gaussian-noise perturbation). e0_dense is perfectly stable (std=0). Under noise-based column perturbation, SST-2 drops 18.92 pp (92.43% -> 73.5%) and MRPC drops 14.29 pp (91.35% -> 77.1%), both with substantial seed sensitivity. This contrasts with the original R3 e2_l1 (binary column zeroing, keep_ratio~0.70, fixed_binary_sparsity, degrade_ratio=0) which showed delta=0.000. The discrepancy reveals that the perturbation mechanism (binary zeroing vs. Gaussian noise injection) dominates the accuracy outcome, not the seed selection. Both results are recorded as perturbation-implementation boundary evidence.",
    "blockers": []
  },
